   "text": "Psychiatry Lithium Toxicity lithium therapeutic-index NSAID thiazide nephrogenic-DI USMLE-style / MedKOS (mood stabilizer safety) A 52 year old woman with bipolar I disorder maintained on lithium develops a coarse tremor, ataxia, confusion, and vomiting one week after starting a thiazide diuretic and ibuprofen for a new diagnosis of hypertension and joint pain. Which mechanism best explains her acute deterioration? A. Reduced renal lithium clearance from thiazide induced volume depletion and NSAID effects, raising lithium to toxic levels B. Displacement of lithium from plasma protein binding by ibuprofen C. Induction of hepatic metabolism of lithium by the thiazide D. Thiazide induced hyperkalemia potentiating lithium E. Formation of a toxic lithium metabolite by CYP3A4 리튬은 치료지수가 좁고 신장으로만 배설된다. thiazide로 인한 용적 감소는 근위세뇨관 Na(과 Li) 재흡수를 늘리고 NSAID는 신혈류를 줄여 리튬 청소율을 낮춰 독성 농도로 올린다. 리튬은 대사·단백결합이 아니라 신배설이 핵심이다."
