   "snippet": "A 24 year old man on fluoxetine is given tramadol for back pain. Within hours he becomes agitated and diaphoretic with a temperature of 39.4 C, tachycardia, dilated pupils, and prominent lower extremity clonus with hyperreflexia. Which diag",
   "text": "Psychiatry Serotonin Syndrome serotonin-syndrome clonus hyperreflexia cyproheptadine NMS USMLE-style / MedKOS (psychopharmacology emergencies) A 24 year old man on fluoxetine is given tramadol for back pain. Within hours he becomes agitated and diaphoretic with a temperature of 39.4 C, tachycardia, dilated pupils, and prominent lower extremity clonus with hyperreflexia. Which diagnosis best fits, and what neuromuscular finding most distinguishes it from its main mimic? A. Serotonin syndrome, distinguished by hyperreflexia and clonus (rapid onset after a serotonergic drug) B. Neuroleptic malignant syndrome, distinguished by hyperreflexia and clonus C. Malignant hyperthermia from an inhaled anesthetic D. Anticholinergic toxicity, distinguished by clonus E. Thyroid storm, distinguished by lead pipe rigidity 세로토닌성 약물(fluoxetine)에 tramadol이 더해진 뒤 수시간 내 발열·자율신경 항진·정신상태 변화와 함께 간대성 경련(clonus)·반사항진이 나타나면 세로토닌 증후군이다. 반사항진·clonus가 NMS(반사저하·경직)와의 결정적 감별점이다."
