   "text": "Obstetrics & Gynecology Ectopic Pregnancy ectopic-pregnancy methotrexate beta-hCG transvaginal-ultrasound USMLE-style / MedKOS (early pregnancy complications) A 26 year old woman with a prior chlamydial pelvic infection presents at 6 weeks by dates with mild left lower quadrant pain and minimal vaginal spotting. She is hemodynamically stable. Serum beta hCG is 1,800 mIU/mL; transvaginal ultrasound shows no intrauterine gestational sac but a small 2 cm adnexal mass without free fluid. Which of the following is the most appropriate management? A. Medical therapy with intramuscular methotrexate, since she is stable with a small unruptured ectopic and no contraindications B. Immediate exploratory laparotomy C. Reassurance and repeat testing in 4 weeks with no intervention D. Dilation and curettage to remove the pregnancy E. High dose oxytocin infusion 혈역학적으로 안정, 파열 없음, 작은 부속기 종괴, 금기 없음인 자궁외임신은 근주 methotrexate로 내과적 치료가 적절하다. β hCG 1,800에서 자궁내 임신낭이 안 보이는 것도 자궁외임신을 시사한다. 불안정·파열이면 수술."
