   "text": "Pathology Amyloidosis amyloidosis AL Congo-red apple-green restrictive-cardiomyopathy USMLE-style / MedKOS (deposition diseases) A 63 year old man has nephrotic range proteinuria, hepatomegaly, macroglossia, and echocardiographic findings of a restrictive cardiomyopathy with low voltage QRS. A fat pad biopsy stained with Congo red shows deposits that display apple green birefringence under polarized light. Serum and urine studies reveal a monoclonal lambda light chain. Which protein most likely composes the deposits? A. Immunoglobulin light chains (AL amyloid) B. Serum amyloid A protein (AA amyloid) C. Transthyretin (ATTR) D. Beta 2 microglobulin E. Beta amyloid (A beta) Congo red에서 편광하 사과녹색 복굴절 + 단클론 경쇄(lambda)는 AL 아밀로이드증으로, 형질세포 이상(다발골수종/MGUS)에서 유래한 면역글로불린 경쇄가 침착한다. 거대혀·제한성 심근병증·신증후군이 특징."
