   "text": "Pathology Retinoblastoma (Two-Hit Hypothesis) retinoblastoma RB1 two-hit tumor-suppressor osteosarcoma USMLE-style / MedKOS (neoplasia, tumor suppressors) A 14 month old girl is found to have bilateral retinoblastomas, and her father was treated for a similar eye tumor in childhood. Genetic testing shows a germline loss of function mutation in one RB1 allele. Which additional event is required within a retinal cell for a tumor to develop, and what is the mechanism? A. Somatic inactivation of the second RB1 allele, because RB1 is a tumor suppressor requiring loss of both copies (Knudson two hit) B. A single activating point mutation in RB1, because RB1 is a proto oncogene C. Amplification of RB1 leading to overexpression D. A gain of function mutation that constitutively activates RB1 E. Methylation that increases RB1 transcription RB1은 종양억제유전자로 Knudson의 two hit 가설을 따른다. 유전성 망막모세포종은 생식세포에 한쪽 대립유전자 결손(first hit)을 이미 갖고, 망막세포에서 두 번째 대립유전자가 체세포 변이로 불활성화(second hit)되면 종양이 생긴다. 그래서 양측성·조기 발병하고 골육종 위험이 높다."
