   "text": "Surgery Acute Mesenteric Ischemia mesenteric-ischemia SMA-embolism atrial-fibrillation lactate USMLE-style / MedKOS (acute abdomen) A 74 year old man with atrial fibrillation who is not on anticoagulation develops sudden severe periumbilical pain. On examination the abdomen is soft with pain that is strikingly out of proportion to the benign findings. Two hours later he passes bloody stool; lactate is elevated with a metabolic acidosis. CT angiography shows an abrupt cutoff of the superior mesenteric artery. Which of the following is the most appropriate management? A. Emergent revascularization (embolectomy or endovascular therapy) with systemic anticoagulation and resection of any nonviable bowel B. Intravenous antibiotics and bowel rest for presumed diverticulitis C. Outpatient workup for chronic mesenteric ischemia D. Reassurance and antispasmodics for irritable bowel syndrome E. Supportive care alone for ischemic colitis 심방세동 환자의 갑작스런 '진찰 소견에 비해 심한 복통' + 젖산 상승 + CTA에서 SMA 폐색은 SMA 색전에 의한 급성 장간막 허혈이다. 시간이 생명이므로 즉시 혈관재개통(색전제거/중재술) + 항응고 + 괴사 장 절제."
