   "text": "Microbiology Exotoxin Mechanism (EF-2 ADP-ribosylation) exotoxin diphtheria Pseudomonas EF-2 ADP-ribosylation USMLE-style / MedKOS (bacterial toxins) A 6 year old unvaccinated child develops a gray pseudomembrane over the tonsils, a bull neck, and, one week later, myocarditis with heart block. The responsible toxin halts host protein synthesis. This toxin shares its precise molecular mechanism with the exotoxin A of Pseudomonas aeruginosa. Which mechanism is it? A. ADP ribosylation of elongation factor 2 (EF 2), inactivating it and arresting translation B. ADP ribosylation of the Gs alpha subunit, persistently raising cAMP C. Removal of an adenine from 28S rRNA of the 60S ribosomal subunit D. Cleavage of SNARE proteins, blocking neurotransmitter release E. Cross linking of MHC class II and the T cell receptor as a superantigen 디프테리아 독소와 Pseudomonas exotoxin A는 모두 EF 2를 ADP ribosylation하여 단백합성을 정지시킨다. 이로써 위막·심근염·신경병이 생긴다. Gs ADP ribosylation(콜레라), 28S rRNA 절단(Shiga), SNARE 절단(보툴리눔), superantigen(TSST 1)과 구별된다."
