   "text": "Microbiology Vancomycin Resistance (VRE) VRE vanA D-Ala-D-Lac resistance peptidoglycan USMLE-style / MedKOS (antimicrobial resistance) A hospitalized patient develops bacteremia with Enterococcus faecium that is resistant to vancomycin. The resistance is mediated by an acquired operon carried on a transposon. Which molecular change most directly accounts for the vancomycin resistance? A. Substitution of the peptidoglycan precursor terminus from D Ala D Ala to D Ala D Lactate B. Production of an extended spectrum beta lactamase C. Acquisition of mecA encoding an altered penicillin binding protein 2a D. Upregulation of a multidrug efflux pump E. Methylation of the 23S ribosomal RNA target VanA형 VRE는 van 오페론이 펩티도글리칸 말단을 D Ala D Ala에서 D Ala D Lac으로 바꿔 vancomycin의 수소결합 친화도를 ~1000배 낮춘다. mecA/PBP2a는 MRSA의 베타락탐 내성이고, erm 메틸화는 macrolide 내성으로 기전이 다르다."
