   "snippet": "A 64 year old man is on prophylactic unfractionated heparin after coronary artery bypass grafting. On postoperative day 6 his platelet count falls from 245,000 to 90,000/uL and he develops a new right lower extremity deep vein thrombosis. A",
   "text": "Hematology Heparin-Induced Thrombocytopenia HIT PF4 thrombosis argatroban warfarin-necrosis USMLE-style / MedKOS (ASH 2018 VTE/HIT guideline) A 64 year old man is on prophylactic unfractionated heparin after coronary artery bypass grafting. On postoperative day 6 his platelet count falls from 245,000 to 90,000/uL and he develops a new right lower extremity deep vein thrombosis. A heparin PF4 antibody ELISA is positive and a serotonin release assay confirms the diagnosis. Which of the following is the most appropriate next step? A. Continue unfractionated heparin at a reduced dose B. Stop heparin and start warfarin immediately C. Stop all heparin and start argatroban; avoid platelet transfusion and defer warfarin until platelet recovery D. Transfuse platelets to correct the thrombocytopenia E. Switch from unfractionated heparin to low molecular weight heparin HIT는 heparin PF4 복합체에 대한 IgG가 혈소판을 Fc 매개로 활성화해 혈전을 유발하는 친혈전성 질환이다. 모든 heparin(LMWH 포함)을 중단하고 비 heparin 항응고제(argatroban 등)를 시작하며, warfarin은 혈소판 회복 전까지 미루고(피부·사지 괴사 위험) 혈소판 수혈은 하지 않는다."
